thin R_500, it decreases to -5% at\nR_500<r<1.5R_500 and then rises back to ~0% at r >~ 2R_500. The scatter of\nb_P(r) between individual relaxed clusters is small -- at the level of <0.03\nwithin R_500, but turns significantly larger (0.25) and highly skewed at r>~\n1.5R_500. For any relaxed cluster we find |b_P(r)| < 15% within R_500, across\ndifferent implementations of input physics in the simulations. [abridged]\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 14 Nov 2012 17:04:34 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 5 Feb 2013 11:20:51 GMT"}],"update_date":"2013-03-05"}
