ric quantities approach zero as the\ntime t approaches zero. This mimics the big bang in that distances approach\nzero. Examples of black and white scaling holes are described in which B(x) is\nplus or minus infinity at a point x.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 14 Nov 2012 18:57:37 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 20 Dec 2012 17:32:13 GMT"}],"update_date":"2012-12-21"}
