tions of HST 10. Apart from\niron, whose gas-phase abundance is ~0.3 dex lower than in the local Orion\nnebula, most other elements in the proplyd do not show substantially different\ngas-phase abundances from the nebula. The abundances of carbon, oxygen and neon\nin HST 10 are practically the same as those in B-type stars in Orion.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 14 Nov 2012 21:03:14 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 22 Jan 2013 19:20:14 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-12"}
