{degrees} of some elements with respect to the continuum limit, we find\nthat the differential-difference Kadomtsev-Petviashvili hierarchies together\nwith their Lax triads, zero curvature representations and all integrable\ncharacteristics go to their continuous counterparts in the continuum limit. We\nalso explain the basic structure deformation of Lie algebras in the continuum\nlimit.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 15 Nov 2012 12:17:32 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Sat, 24 Nov 2012 08:46:20 GMT"}],"update_date":"2014-01-27"}
